class Solution {
    public int canBeTypedWords(String text, String brokenLetters) {
        boolean[] broken = new boolean[26];
        for (char c : brokenLetters.toCharArray()) {
            broken[c - 'a'] = true;
        }
        int count = 0;
        for (String word : text.split(" ")) {
            boolean valid = true;
            for (char c : word.toCharArray()) {
                if (broken[c - 'a']) {
                    valid = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (valid) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n + m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the broken letters and the words in the text once, using a boolean array to mark broken letters and checking each word against this array, resulting in a linear time complexity. The space used is constant as it is limited by the size of the alphabet. 
